commentary: Kumar to Powell, OUT shorter now, slants it into the corridor outside off. Slashes at it, and misses. Or has he missed it? India have reviewed - they appealed belatedly for caught behind, and it wasn't given. Didn't look like the most confident appeal, but they reviewed confidently, if that makes any sense, and Snicko proves them right. A fairly discernible edge, even in terms of noise, shows up clearly on Snicko. Outside edge, close to the toe end. Not much room there, and he ended up slashing with an angled bat

commentary: Kuldeep Yadav to Hope, OUT appeal for leg before, Gaffaney says not out and India have asked for a review. Front foot is fine. Nicely flighted and dips extremely late. Hope gets down for a sweep but is done in by the last-minute dip. Lands just in front of the pad, sneaks from beneath the willow as the batsman misses the sweep and spins in. Looks pretty close, he could be gone here. No bat involved, certainly. Hitting middle and leg, so the on-field call will be reversed
